A4 inhibitor, a progressive dosage reduction may be required over a longer period if the corticosteroid is to be withdrawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression.', 'Metabolism', 'The possibility of increased corticosteroid effects should be considered during coadministration with potent and moderate CYP450 3A4 inhibitors.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/142742/', '', 'Fluocinolone acetonide, Fluorometholone, Fluocinolone acetonide, Diclofenac', 'Citalopram, Sertraline, Maprotiline, Fluoxetine, St. John''s Wort, Milnacipran, Vortioxetine, Levomilnacipran, Doxepin, Duloxetine, Isocarboxazid, More', 1767369485);
